<span id="freeTextContainer14164789619355293918">I will start off by saying that this is a good book which I did not like that much.<br/>This story is told from a point of view of a young Bengali boy whose ancestry is from Dhaka (current Bangladesh). This is majorly about two families, one British and one Indian, and their inter-relations.<br/>The first half of this novel could not captivate my attention. The second half was way better with the pace of the narration. <br/>This book is in the same school of <i>Rushdie&apos;s Midnight&apos;s children</i>, but fails to reach th</span>
  <span id="freeText14164789619355293918" style="display:none">I will start off by saying that this is a good book which I did not like that much.<br />This story is told from a point of view of a young Bengali boy whose ancestry is from Dhaka (current Bangladesh). This is majorly about two families, one British and one Indian, and their inter-relations.<br />The first half of this novel could not captivate my attention. The second half was way better with the pace of the narration. <br />This book is in the same school of <i>Rushdie's Midnight's children</i>, but fails to reach the same apogee. <br />Overall a decent read, especially if you are Bengali.</span>
